      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i need help with this python function for my uni coding lab. the grader is super strict about the time limit and it keeps failing my submission because the complexity is too high for large inputs. can u optimize it so it passes the runtime tests? thanks.\n\n```python\ndef find_prime_factors(n):\n    factors = []\n    d = 2\n    temp = n\n    while temp > 1:\n        while temp % d == 0:\n            factors.append(d)\n            temp //= d\n        d += 1\n    return factors\n```",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can optimize your function to reduce its time complexity. The main issue with your function is that it checks every number up to `n` in each iteration, which is unnecessary. We can stop checking once we've found a factor. Here's the optimized version:\n\n```python\ndef find_prime_factors(n):\n    factors = []\n    d = 2\n    while d * d <= n:\n        while n % d == 0:\n            factors.append(d)\n            n //= d\n        d += 1\n    if n > 1:\n        factors.append(n)\n    return factors\n```\n\nThis optimized function works by only checking up to the square root of `n`, which significantly reduces its time complexity. It also handles the case where `n` itself is a prime number.",
